    Answer contents

    Go (Golang) is a programming language created at Google by Google developers and other programmers. It is free and open-source, and currently being maintained by Google. Some of its features are:
    • Simplicity. Go has a simpler syntax compared to other compiled programming languages. 2
    • Concurrency. Go supports the built-in concurrency model with the help of GoRoutines. 152
    • Garbage collection. Go has a built-in garbage collector and memory safety. 132
    • Unicode support. Go supports Unicode by default, which means that the programmer does not need any extra code for printing characters from multiple human languages or symbols. 3
    • Standard library. The standard Go library offers many packages that simplify the work of the developer. 13
    Go can be used to build web applications and it provides a simple web server for testing purposes. It can also be used for writing UNIX systems software. 3
    Some of the resources where one can find information about Go are:
    • go.dev; 1
    • medium.com; 2
    • linode.com; 3
    • github.com. 4
